CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, July 25, 1959, pg. 1, reads: "Dr. Brown's Associate - Seeing the education of his three children being jeopardized by the South's stand against school integration, Dr. Leon W. Williams, left, internal medicine specialist, quit as Chief of Pulmonary Disease Services at the integrated 1,912 bed VA Hospital at Tuskegee, Ala., to become an associate in private practice with Dr. W. Roderick Brown, right, local TB specialist. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Dr. Leon W. Williams and Dr. W. Roderick Brown, standing in front of X-ray machine
